  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nErigon version: `./erigon --version`\r\nerigon version 2022.99.99-dev-087105d1\r\n\r\nOS & Version: Windows/Linux/OSX\r\nUbuntu 20.04\r\n\r\nCommit hash : \r\ncommit 087105d1f31d83ff88ceeca30dfe36dc01de28d7 \r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nWhen I close a subscribtion, it close it and Erigon continue to run. If I close my application with a subscription open, Erigon should not panic\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nWhen I close a subscription, from my web3 client or if I kill my application, Erigon panic and crash.\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\nOpen a subscription like \"new heads\" and close it.\r\n\r\n#### Backtrace\r\n\r\n````\r\nEROR[06-30|19:37:45.878] catch panic                              err=\"close of closed channel\" stack=\"[log_panic.go:24 panic.go:838 chan.go:364 eth_filters.go:173 asm_amd64.s:1571]\"\r\nINFO[06-30|19:37:45.878] Got interrupt, shutting down...\r\n\r\n````\r\nThis issue is happening only on BSC, I have another Erigon node synced on Eth mainnet on another server who works as expected.",
